<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Quadratic Equations — UltimateEdge School</title>
<style>
* { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
body { font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; background: #0d1117; color: #e6edf3; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; }
.slide { display: none; min-height: 100vh; padding: 48px 40px; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; }
.slide.active { display: flex; }
.slide-num { font-size: .75rem; font-weight: 700; color: #58a6ff; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .08em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 16px; line-height: 1.1; }
h2 { font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 700; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 14px; }
p  { color: #8b949e; font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 12px; line-height: 1.7; max-width: 600px; }
.formula { background: #161b22; border: 1px solid #30363d; border-radius: 10px; padding: 20px 28px; font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; font-size: 1.3rem; color: #79c0ff; margin: 20px 0; display: inline-block; }
.step-list { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px; margin: 16px 0; max-width: 600px; }
.step-list li { display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start; }
.step-num { background: #1a56ff; color: #fff; width: 28px; height: 28px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: 700; font-size: .85rem; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px; }
.example-box { background: #161b22; border: 1px solid #30363d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 24px 28px; margin: 20px 0; max-width: 620px; }
.example-box h3 { color: #79c0ff; font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: .04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
.highlight { color: #ffa657; font-weight: 700; }
.controls { position: fixed; bottom: 24px; right: 24px; display: flex; gap: 10px; }
.ctrl-btn { background: #1a56ff; color: #fff; border: none; border-radius: 8px; padding: 10px 20px; font-weight: 700; font-size: .9rem; cursor: pointer; transition: background .15s; }
.ctrl-btn:hover { background: #1040cc; }
.ctrl-btn.secondary { background: rgba(255,255,255,.1); }
.ctrl-btn:disabled { opacity: .4; cursor: not-allowed; }
.progress-bar { position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; height: 3px; background: rgba(255,255,255,.1); }
.progress-fill { height: 100%; background: #1a56ff; transition: width .3s; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="progress-bar"><div class="progress-fill" id="prog"></div></div>

<!-- Slide 1: Title -->
<div class="slide active" id="slide-1">
  <div class="slide-num">Mathematics · Quadratic Equations · Grade 3</div>
  <h1>Quadratic Equations</h1>
  <p>A quadratic equation is a polynomial of degree 2. It takes the form <span class="highlight">ax² + bx + c = 0</span>, where a ≠ 0.</p>
  <p>By the end of this lesson, you will be able to solve quadratic equations using three methods: factorisation, completing the square, and the quadratic formula.</p>
  <div class="formula">ax² + bx + c = 0</div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 2: Factorisation -->
<div class="slide" id="slide-2">
  <div class="slide-num">Method 1 · Factorisation</div>
  <h2>Solving by Factorisation</h2>
  <p>Factorisation works when the quadratic can be written as a product of two brackets.</p>
  <ul class="step-list">
    <li><div class="step-num">1</div><div>Write the equation in standard form: ax² + bx + c = 0</div></li>
    <li><div class="step-num">2</div><div>Find two numbers that multiply to give <span class="highlight">ac</span> and add to give <span class="highlight">b</span></div></li>
    <li><div class="step-num">3</div><div>Rewrite the middle term using these two numbers</div></li>
    <li><div class="step-num">4</div><div>Factorise by grouping, then set each factor to zero</div></li>
  </ul>
  <div class="example-box">
    <h3>Example: Solve x² - 5x + 6 = 0</h3>
    <p>Find two numbers that multiply to 6 and add to -5: <span class="highlight">-2 and -3</span></p>
    <p>So: (x - 2)(x - 3) = 0</p>
    <p>Therefore: <span class="highlight">x = 2 or x = 3</span></p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 3: Completing the Square -->
<div class="slide" id="slide-3">
  <div class="slide-num">Method 2 · Completing the Square</div>
  <h2>Completing the Square</h2>
  <p>This method always works and is used when factorisation is not obvious.</p>
  <ul class="step-list">
    <li><div class="step-num">1</div><div>Divide all terms by <span class="highlight">a</span> if a ≠ 1</div></li>
    <li><div class="step-num">2</div><div>Move constant <span class="highlight">c/a</span> to the right side</div></li>
    <li><div class="step-num">3</div><div>Add <span class="highlight">(b/2a)²</span> to both sides</div></li>
    <li><div class="step-num">4</div><div>Write the left side as a perfect square and solve</div></li>
  </ul>
  <div class="example-box">
    <h3>Example: Solve x² + 6x + 5 = 0</h3>
    <p>x² + 6x = -5</p>
    <p>x² + 6x + 9 = -5 + 9 = 4</p>
    <p>(x + 3)² = 4 → x + 3 = ±2</p>
    <p>Therefore: <span class="highlight">x = -1 or x = -5</span></p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 4: Quadratic Formula -->
<div class="slide" id="slide-4">
  <div class="slide-num">Method 3 · Quadratic Formula</div>
  <h2>The Quadratic Formula</h2>
  <p>The most powerful method — works for any quadratic equation.</p>
  <div class="formula">x = (-b ± √(b² - 4ac)) / 2a</div>
  <p>The expression <span class="highlight">b² - 4ac</span> is called the <strong>discriminant</strong>:</p>
  <ul class="step-list">
    <li><div class="step-num">+</div><div>If b² - 4ac > 0 → <span class="highlight">two distinct real roots</span></div></li>
    <li><div class="step-num">=</div><div>If b² - 4ac = 0 → <span class="highlight">one repeated root</span></div></li>
    <li><div class="step-num">−</div><div>If b² - 4ac < 0 → <span class="highlight">no real roots</span></div></li>
  </ul>
  <div class="example-box">
    <h3>Example: Solve 2x² - 3x - 2 = 0</h3>
    <p>a=2, b=-3, c=-2</p>
    <p>x = (3 ± √(9 + 16)) / 4 = (3 ± √25) / 4 = (3 ± 5) / 4</p>
    <p>Therefore: <span class="highlight">x = 2 or x = -0.5</span></p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Slide 5: Summary -->
<div class="slide" id="slide-5">
  <div class="slide-num">Summary · Quadratic Equations</div>
  <h2>What We Covered Today</h2>
  <ul class="step-list">
    <li><div class="step-num">1</div><div><strong>Factorisation</strong> — fastest when it works. Look for factors of ac that sum to b.</div></li>
    <li><div class="step-num">2</div><div><strong>Completing the Square</strong> — always works, gives vertex form. Useful for graphing.</div></li>
    <li><div class="step-num">3</div><div><strong>Quadratic Formula</strong> — the universal solver. Memorise: x = (-b ± √(b²-4ac)) / 2a</div></li>
  </ul>
  <p style="margin-top:20px">You are now ready to solve any quadratic equation that appears in JAMB, WAEC, or NECO.</p>
  <button onclick="onLessonEnd()" style="margin-top:28px;background:#00c97a;color:#fff;border:none;border-radius:10px;padding:14px 32px;font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;cursor:pointer">
    ✓ Mark as Complete — Earn XP
  </button>
</div>

<div class="controls">
  <button class="ctrl-btn secondary" id="btn-prev" onclick="prevSlide()" disabled>← Back</button>
  <button class="ctrl-btn" id="btn-next" onclick="nextSlide()">Next →</button>
</div>

<script>
let current = 1;
const total = 5;

function updateUI() {
  for (let i = 1; i <= total; i++) {
    const el = document.getElementById('slide-' + i);
    if (el) el.classList.toggle('active', i === current);
  }
  document.getElementById('btn-prev').disabled = current === 1;
  document.getElementById('btn-next').textContent = current === total ? 'Finish' : 'Next →';
  document.getElementById('prog').style.width = ((current / total) * 100) + '%';
}

function nextSlide() {
  if (current < total) { current++; updateUI(); }
  else onLessonEnd();
}

function prevSlide() {
  if (current > 1) { current--; updateUI(); }
}

function onLessonEnd() {
  window.parent.postMessage({ type: 'lesson_completed', topic: 'quadratics' }, '*');
  document.getElementById('btn-next').textContent = '✓ Completed!';
  document.getElementById('btn-next').style.background = '#00c97a';
}

/* Keyboard navigation */
document.addEventListener('keydown', e => {
  if (e.key === 'ArrowRight' || e.key === 'ArrowDown') nextSlide();
  if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft'  || e.key === 'ArrowUp')   prevSlide();
});

updateUI();
</script>
</body>
</html>
